 well, his second wife Sarah Hooker (H00432) being his maternal first cousin."}],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[{"war":"American Revolutionary War","war_id":"WAR004","rank":"Private","rank_year_start":1776,"rank_year_end":1779,"unit":"Multiple — Capt. Gad Stanley's Co (1776), Capt. Lankton's Co under Col. Noadiah Hooker's Regt (1777), Capt. Matthew Cole's Co (1779)","notes":"Three documented enlistments: (1) June 1776 — four months in Capt. Gad Stanley's Company at the Battle of Harlem Heights; (2) summer 1777 — three months in Capt. Lankton's Company under Col. Noadiah Hooker's Regiment; (3) July 1779 — ten days in Capt. Matthew Cole's Company at the Battle of New Haven (Tryon's Raid). Placed on the federal pension list in 1838. DAR Ancestor #A045110. Source: Berlin-Peck Memorial Library."}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"military","header":"Three Revolutionary War enlistments and 1838 pension","body":"Hooker Gilbert enlisted three times during the Revolution: four months in June 1776 in Capt. Gad Stanley's Company at the Battle of Harlem Heights; three months in summer 1777 in Capt. Lankton's Company under Col. Noadiah Hooker's Regiment; and ten days in July 1779 in Capt. Matthew Cole's Company at the Battle of New Haven during Tryon's Raid. He was placed on the federal pension list in 1838 and is recorded as DAR Ancestor #A045110."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Married his first cousin Sarah Hooker in 1807","body":"Hooker Gilbert's first wife Candace Sage died May 15, 1805. Two years later on June 30, 1807 he married Sarah Hooker — his maternal first cousin and the daughter of his uncle Samuel Hooker Jr. The marriage united two grandchildren of Samuel Hooker via his daughter Elizabeth Hooker Gilbert and his son Samuel Hooker Jr."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Both spouses died within two days December 1840","body":"Sarah Hooker died December 4, 1840 at Kensington Connecticut at age 77. Hooker Gilbert followed her two days later on December 6, 1840 at age 86 — together they had been married for thirty-three years."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"Two grandchildren of Samuel Hooker reunited 1807","body":"Hooker Gilbert and Sarah Hooker were the marriage point where two branches of the Hooker line came back together. His mother Elizabeth and her father Samuel Jr. had been siblings — both children of Samuel Hooker of Kensington. The cousin marriage produced no documented children of its own but closed a fifty-year gap between the two branches."}],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM237"},"slug":"hooker-gilbert-1751"},"X02713":{"id":"X02713","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Candace","last_name":"Gilbert","maiden_name":"Sage","married_names":["Gilbert"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Candace Sage Gilbert"},"birth":{},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1805,"month":5,"day":15,"city":"Kensington","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H00420","date_year":1776,"date_month":11,"date_day":1,"location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1805,"children_ids":["H01109","H01110","H01111","H01112","H01113","H01114"]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1